The paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques in the context of IoT, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the case where data traces are instantiations of Gaussian random variables, which suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the structure of dependency graphs, which suggests that it may fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with statistical matching, which is a technique used in data science and statistics, suggesting that it may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
